This is an example of how to use siesta to wantibexos interface

to run siesta2wtb.py it's mandatory to have sisl installed (0.16.2 version - recommended)

1) Go to siesta folder and run siesta dft calculation

mandatory flags: 

CDF.Save true
CDF.Compress 9
SaveHS true
SaveRho true

2) Finished siesta calculation:

 - copy siesta2wtb.py inside siesta folder
 - in siesta folder execute: python3 siesta2wtb.py calc.fdf
 - it will generate the following outputs: tb-xx.dat, system-info-xx.dat, basis_set-xx
 - xx= np for non-polarized, sp for spin-polarized, soc for spin-orbit couplinf
 - tb-xx.dat: this file contains the hamiltonian to be used in wantibexos
 - system-info-xx.dat: contains aditional information from sisl
 - basis_set-xx: this file informs the basis set that the hamiltonian is written
 
3) Copy tb-xx.dat for wtb folder and run wantibexos 

 - wtb.x < input.dat

